children.text: The roofing sheets have not been adequately fixed/fastened in accordance with the Building Code of Australia.
Part 3.5.1.5 Fixing of metal sheet roofing of the NCC’s Building Code of Australia (BCA), requires that
‘Metal sheet roofing must be fixed at spacings in accordance with Table 3.5.1.4’ ;
The entire roof should be fully checked to ensure that all fixings/fasteners are installed in accordance with the requirements of the BCA.
